     Wink is back at it again with the long awaited follow up to?516 Acid?.
     This is the first time these tracks will be released on vinyl.
     ?Swirl? was featured on Josh Wink?s acclaimed mix compilation Profound 
     Sounds Volume 3, but this is the first time a full version of the track
     will be released. In Wink?s signature style of creating tension, he full 
     delivers on Swirl. The track slowly builds and takes off when Wink adds 
     in his signature 303 bass line. Like one of Wink?s DJ sets It goes
     through many peaks and valleys, but it is the tension that is created
     that will drive the floor nuts. The B side is ?Have To Get Back?, which
     had been released on Minus Records Min to Mac comp, but only in an
     instrumental form. This is the very rare vocal version of that track.
     Again Wink provides the tension in this dark affair. The addition of the
     eerie vocal will remind people why he is the master of the bugged out
     production.
